commit.message: Merge branch 'master' of github.com:phn/jdcal
Removed references to easy_install.

Remove deprecated license_file from setup.cfg (#22)

Starting with wheel 0.32.0 (2018-09-29), the "license_file" option is
deprecated.

https://wheel.readthedocs.io/en/stable/news.html

The wheel will continue to include LICENSE, it is now included
automatically:

https://wheel.readthedocs.io/en/stable/user_guide.html#including-license-files-in-the-generated-wheel-file

Fixed E741 ambiguous variable name 'l' in jdcal.py.

Ignore E722 (bare except) and E501 (line too long) in test_jdcal.py.

Simplify Travis CI configuration and add testing for Python 3.8 (#24)

Can drop deprecated sudo option:

https://blog.travis-ci.com/2018-11-19-required-linux-infrastructure-migration

Xenial is now the default, can drop the dist option:

https://blog.travis-ci.com/2019-04-15-xenial-default-build-environment

Use tox as the single entry point to run tests. This unifies Travis
testing with local testing.

Use the shorter alias pypy3 & pypy to test against the most recently
supported PyPy versions.

Test against Python 3.8 and add the trove classifier.

Use builtin mod operator (#23)

The Python docs recommend using the builtin mod operator (%) for
integers.

https://docs.python.org/3/library/math.html#math.fmod

> For this reason, function fmod() is generally preferred when working
> with floats, while Python’s x % y is preferred when working with
> integers.

Simplify: Replace ipart() builtin function int() (#20)

The function's docstring was: "Return integer part of given number."

Python has a builtin function for this: int(). From the docs:

https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#int

> If x defines __int__(), int(x) returns x.__int__(). If x defines
> __trunc__(), it returns x.__trunc__(). For floating point numbers,
> this truncates towards zero.

Reuse math import (#21)

Don't try to import a 2nd time, the module is already available.
Update to version 1.4.1 and changes noted in CHANGELOG.txt.

Remove unused and undocumented function fpart() (#18)

Remove fpart() from module and tests.

Update Travis CI tests to remove Python 2.6 and 3.3 and add Python 3.7 (#17)

* Update Travis CI tests to remove Python 2.6 and 3.3 and add Python 3.7

* Install latest setuptools to avoid race condition https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/951\#issuecomment-299653469

* Remove sudo: true as it's no longer necessary

* Simplify Travis CI builds for Python 3.7

* Fix PyPy versions and add Python 3.7 to the Python list.

Update pypi.python.org URL to pypi.org (#15)

For details on the new PyPI, see the blog post:

https://pythoninsider.blogspot.ca/2018/04/new-pypi-launched-legacy-pypi-shutting.html

Remove Py3.2 from travis and setup.py classifier list.

The code does work on Py3.2 but attr (dependency of py.test)
doesn't work on Py3.2. So removing 3.2 from .travis.yml and
setup.py trove classifier.

Version 1.4.

Wheel support.
Test more Python versions on travis.
Add more Python versions in classifiers in setup.py.
Change version number in jdcal.py.
Add test to compare gcal2jd with astropy._erfa.cal2jd.

Add universal wheel support (#11)

Add universal wheel support by adding information to "setup.cfg".

Trim trailing white space throughout the project (#12)

Many editors clean up trailing white space on save. By removing it all
in one go, it helps keep future diffs cleaner by avoiding spurious white
space changes on unrelated lines.

Enable pip cache in Travis CI (#13)

Slightly speed up builds and reduce load on PyPI servers.

For more information, see:

https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/caching/#pip-cache

Update Python versions (#10)

+ Add Python 3.6.
+ Change http to https.
Minor fix for extraneous text in CHANGELOG.rst.

New version 1.3.

1) Use setuptools instead of distutils.
   I will continue non-wheel on pypi since I am not familiar with
   wheels, and can't spend time on it if this breaks someone's
   setup.
2) Made entry in changelog.

Merge pull request #7 from James-Dengel/wheel_changes

change to use setuptools so that we can create a wheel
change to use setuptools so that we can create a wheel
